               <head>Commentary on Rumi’s Masnavi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Sharḥ-i Mas̲navī by Muḥammad Nūr Allāh Aḥrārī Akbar'ābādī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1040B-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_305037797">Muḥammad Nūr Allāh Aḥrārī Akbar'ābādī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_305037797">محمّد نور الله احرارى اكبر آبادى </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20446">Sharḥ-i Mas̲navī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20446">شرح مثنوى</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Commentary on the <title>Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title> of Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī (d. 670/1271) by <persName key="person_305037797" role="aut">Muḥammad Nūr Allāh Aḥrārī [Akbarābādī]</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 164v): completed 4 Z̲ī al-Qaʿdah in RY 45 [of <persName key="person_6178410" role="oth">Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I</persName>], (1114)/22 March 1703. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Scribal shikastah āmīz. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations and corrections in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Brown leather binding, combed marble paper pasted as doublure. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios mostly bound, but gathering detached from binding; some loose folios, cropped, wormholes, later repairs. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
